{
  "texts": [
    "Automatic AI detection systems identified ChatGPT stimuli as AIgenerated 10% of the time, whereas none of the same stimuli humanized using Undetectable.AI were identified as AI-generated.",
    "The false-negative rate was therefore 90% for ChatGPT and 100% for Undetectable.AI.",
    "This result aligns with the work of Mitrovic et al. (2023), who showed that rephrasing makes ChatGPT texts more difficult to detect.",
    "While it is largely unclear how Undetecable.AI works, we were able to observe that it does add spelling and grammar mistakes to the text.",
    "Their frequency was similar to that seen in text written by humans."
  ]
}